CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1957, pg. 1 reads: "Fond Memento - Miss Rosella Bush sits in one of the rocking chairs, which is among her collection of valuable antiques, and displays the strap which she has used daily for the past 40 years to bind some of the mail which she delivered on R.D. 1. She was given permission to keep it as a souvenir of her days as a rural mail carrier."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Rosella Bush wearing eyeglasses, plaid housecoat, and striped socks, seated in rocking chair holding light colored mail strap in her home, 27 McNutt Street, Houston, Pennsylvania
